  "summary": "This chunk contains index entries and scattered references to spirits, ritual texts, tools, and concepts from Kieckhefer’s *Forbidden Rites*, with emphasis on the Munich Handbook (CLM 849) and related necromantic traditions. Named entities include spirits like Castiel, Mirael, Paymon, Lucifer, Satan, Semiforas, and Oriens; ritual texts such as *Liber consecrationum*, *Liber de angelis*, *Key of Solomon*, *Testament of Solomon*, *Lemegeton*, and *Rawlinson MS D 252*; tools like circles, rings, swords, mirrors, and vessels; and conceptual elements in conjuration (e.g., declaration, invocation, instruction). The index highlights recurring ritual components across medieval magical manuscripts.",
